# Internationalization — new strings

When adding **new** user-facing copy or translation keys:

1. Add the key and **English source text** only in `src/lib/i18n/dictionaries/dictionary.json`.
2. **Do not** add the same key to `en.json`, `es.json`, `fr.json`, `de.json`, or any other file under `src/lib/i18n/dictionaries/` except `dictionary.json`.

Other locale files are updated automatically by the translation pipeline in CI/CD after changes land. Manually editing them for new keys is redundant and can conflict with automation.

Use `useAppTranslation` / `translate()` as documented in `src/lib/i18n/dictionaries/LANGUAGES.md`.

```typescript
// After adding "myFeature.title": "Hello" to dictionary.json
const { t } = useAppTranslation();
return <p>{t("myFeature.title")}</p>;
```

**Exception:** If you are deliberately fixing or adjusting an **existing** entry in a specific locale file per team process, that is separate from adding new keys—follow whatever your PR review requires.
